<emphasis id="B904022DFF92FFB7FCD0FCB7FC190D02" box="[826,970,778,800]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="500">
<typeStatus id="54CB609DFF92FFB7FCD0FCB7FCBC0D3D" box="[826,879,779,800]" pageId="55" pageNumber="500">Type</typeStatus>
locality
</emphasis>
: 
<location id="8EAF88E4FF92FFB7FC33FCB6FB520D3D" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03D96F29FF92FFB7FCA4FD65FB69096D:8EAF88E4FF92FFB7FC33FCB6FB520D3D" box="[985,1153,778,800]" country="Italy" name="Gulf of Naples" pageId="55" pageNumber="500">Gulf of Naples</location>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F3679EAFFF92FFB7FB64FCB6FB160D3D" box="[1166,1221,778,800]" name="Italy" pageId="55" pageNumber="500">Italy</collectingCountry>
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCFDE3FFF92FFB7FCD0FC85FBF80DD4" blockId="55.[826,1442,824,969]" pageId="55" pageNumber="500">
<emphasis id="B904022DFF92FFB7FCD0FC85FC010D53" box="[826,978,825,846]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="500">Known range</emphasis>
: Atlantic coasts of 
<collectingCountry id="F3679EAFFF92FFB7FB32FC84FAFB0D50" box="[1240,1320,824,845]" name="France" pageId="55" pageNumber="500">France</collectingCountry>
south to Atlantic coast of 
<collectingCountry id="F3679EAFFF92FFB7FC11FCEBFB880D71" box="[1019,1115,855,876]" name="Morocco" pageId="55" pageNumber="500">Morocco</collectingCountry>
, and widespread throughout the Mediterranean including 
<collectingCountry id="F3679EAFFF92FFB7FB74FCC9FB3D0D97" box="[1182,1262,885,906]" name="Greece" pageId="55" pageNumber="500">Greece</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F3679EAFFF92FFB7FB15FCC9FAE70D96" box="[1279,1332,885,907]" name="Italy" pageId="55" pageNumber="500">Italy</collectingCountry>
, Adriatic Sea, Ionian Sea, Aegean Sea and south-east of Black Sea (
<bibRefCitation id="EFE1A3CEFF92FFB7FC99FC0FFBCC0DD4" author="Ngoc-Ho N" box="[883,1055,947,969]" pageId="55" pageNumber="500" pagination="439 - 555" refId="ref73457" refString="Ngoc-Ho N. 2003. European and Meditterranean Thalassinidea (Crustacea, Decapoda). Zoosystema 25: 439 - 555." type="journal article" year="2003">Ngoc-Ho, 2003</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCFDE3FFF92FFB7FCD0FC5DFC270A09" blockId="55.[826,1442,993,1045]" pageId="55" pageNumber="500">
<emphasis id="B904022DFF92FFB7FCD0FC5DFBAF0DEB" box="[826,1148,993,1014]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="500">Occurrence at vents or seeps</emphasis>
: shallow-water vents in the 
<collectingRegion id="49B410DDFF92FFB7FC8DFBBCFC6F0A08" box="[871,956,1024,1045]" country="Greece" name="Voreio Aigaio" pageId="55" pageNumber="500">Aegean</collectingRegion>
Sea.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCFDE3FFF92FFB7FCD0FB91FB330A5E" blockId="55.[826,1248,1069,1091]" box="[826,1248,1069,1091]" pageId="55" pageNumber="500">
<emphasis id="B904022DFF92FFB7FCD0FB91FC4E0A5F" box="[826,925,1069,1090]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="500">Material</emphasis>
: See below under Remarks.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCFDE3FFF92FFB7FCD0FBE7FAD80841" blockId="55.[826,1442,1115,1904]" pageId="55" pageNumber="500">
<emphasis id="B904022DFF92FFB7FCD0FBE7FC4C0A6D" box="[826,927,1115,1136]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="500">Remarks</emphasis>
: 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE1A3CEFF92FFB7FC5EFBE7FB480A6C" author="Dando PR &amp; Huges JA &amp; Thiermann F" box="[948,1179,1115,1137]" pageId="55" pageNumber="500" pagination="303 - 317" refId="ref64294" refString="Dando PR, Huges JA, Thiermann F. 1995. Preliminary observations on biological communities at shallow hydrothermal vents in the Aegean Sea. In: Parson LM, Walker CL, Dixon DR, eds. Hydrothermal vents and processes. Geological Society Special Publication No. 87: 303 - 317." type="book chapter" year="1995">
Dando 
<emphasis id="B904022DFF92FFB7FBE7FBE0FBED0A6D" box="[1037,1086,1115,1137]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="500">et al</emphasis>
. (1995)
</bibRefCitation>
reported 
<taxonomicName id="4C70A5BCFF92FFB7FAF0FBE7FC4F0A8D" authorityName="GIARD &amp; BONNIER" authorityYear="1890" class="Malacostraca" family="Callianassidae" genus="Callianassa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="55" pageNumber="500" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="truncata">
<emphasis id="B904022DFF92FFB7FAF0FBE7FC4F0A8D" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="500">Callianassa truncata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as one of several species collected from shallow water (intertidal to approximately 
<quantity id="4C8873DAFF92FFB7FAE0FB25FA810AB3" box="[1290,1362,1177,1199]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.15" pageId="55" pageNumber="500" unit="m" value="115.0">115 m</quantity>
) vents around the islands of Milos and Santorini in the Hellenic Volcanic Arc of the 
<collectingRegion id="49B410DDFF92FFB7FBBEFB6AFB7A0AF6" box="[1108,1193,1238,1259]" country="Greece" name="Voreio Aigaio" pageId="55" pageNumber="500">Aegean</collectingRegion>
Sea. None of the species collected by them, including 
<taxonomicName id="4C70A5BCFF92FFB7FB0AFB49FAB30B17" authorityName="GIARD &amp; BONNIER" authorityYear="1890" box="[1248,1376,1269,1290]" class="Malacostraca" family="Callianassidae" genus="Callianassa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="55" pageNumber="500" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="truncata">
<emphasis id="B904022DFF92FFB7FB0AFB49FAB30B17" box="[1248,1376,1269,1290]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="500">C. truncata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, was considered endemic to hydrothermal vents. The specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="4C70A5BCFF92FFB7FC41FA8EFBF90B55" authorityName="GIARD &amp; BONNIER" authorityYear="1890" box="[939,1066,1330,1352]" class="Malacostraca" family="Callianassidae" genus="Callianassa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="55" pageNumber="500" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="truncata">
<emphasis id="B904022DFF92FFB7FC41FA8EFBF90B55" box="[939,1066,1330,1352]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="500">C. truncata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
came from core samples taken around a single vent at 
<quantity id="4C8873DAFF92FFB7FBAFFAEDFBAC0B7B" box="[1093,1151,1361,1382]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" pageId="55" pageNumber="500" unit="m" value="12.0">12 m</quantity>
in the centre of Paleohori Bay. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE1A3CEFF92FFB7FC97FAD3FBBD0B98" author="Dando PR &amp; Huges JA &amp; Thiermann F" box="[893,1134,1391,1413]" pageId="55" pageNumber="500" pagination="303 - 317" refId="ref64294" refString="Dando PR, Huges JA, Thiermann F. 1995. Preliminary observations on biological communities at shallow hydrothermal vents in the Aegean Sea. In: Parson LM, Walker CL, Dixon DR, eds. Hydrothermal vents and processes. Geological Society Special Publication No. 87: 303 - 317." type="book chapter" year="1995">
Dando 
<emphasis id="B904022DFF92FFB7FC31FACCFBDF0B99" box="[987,1036,1391,1413]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="500">et al</emphasis>
. (1995)
</bibRefCitation>
noted that ‘burrows of 
<taxonomicName id="4C70A5BCFF92FFB7FCD0FA32FC690BB9" authorityName="GIARD &amp; BONNIER" authorityYear="1890" box="[826,954,1422,1444]" class="Malacostraca" family="Callianassidae" genus="Callianassa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="55" pageNumber="500" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="truncata">
<emphasis id="B904022DFF92FFB7FCD0FA32FC690BB9" box="[826,954,1422,1444]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="500">C. truncata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were confined to the lower temperature region of the transect, &lt;40°C at 
<quantity id="4C8873DAFF92FFB7FB34FA11FAF90BDF" box="[1246,1322,1453,1474]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="55" pageNumber="500" unit="cm" value="10.0">10 cm</quantity>
sediment depth.’ Although 
<specimenCount id="9D7615B6FF92FFB7FBECFA77FB120BFC" box="[1030,1217,1483,1505]" pageId="55" pageNumber="500" type="generic">eight specimens</specimenCount>
are listed in their table 3, it is not clear if any of the specimens were retained. The 
<collectingRegion id="49B410DDFF92FFB7FC3CF9B5FBF80803" box="[982,1067,1545,1566]" country="Greece" name="Voreio Aigaio" pageId="55" pageNumber="500">Aegean</collectingRegion>
is an area of great volcanic activity; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE1A3CEFF92FFB7FC81F99BFB9F0820" author="Dando PR &amp; Huges JA &amp; Thiermann F" box="[875,1100,1575,1597]" pageId="55" pageNumber="500" pagination="303 - 317" refId="ref64294" refString="Dando PR, Huges JA, Thiermann F. 1995. Preliminary observations on biological communities at shallow hydrothermal vents in the Aegean Sea. In: Parson LM, Walker CL, Dixon DR, eds. Hydrothermal vents and processes. Geological Society Special Publication No. 87: 303 - 317." type="book chapter" year="1995">
Dando 
<emphasis id="B904022DFF92FFB7FC28F994FC210821" box="[962,1010,1575,1597]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="500">et al</emphasis>
. (1995)
</bibRefCitation>
listed several other shallow volcanic regions yet to be fully explored.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCFDE3FFF92FFB7FCB9F9D9FB69096D" blockId="55.[826,1442,1115,1904]" pageId="55" pageNumber="500">
This species was transferred to the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C70A5BCFF92FFB7FAA3F9D9FC5A0884" authorityName="Heard &amp; R.B.Manning" authorityYear="1998" class="Malacostraca" family="Callianassidae" genus="Necallianassa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="55" pageNumber="500" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B904022DFF92FFB7FAA3F9D9FC5A0884" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="500">Necallianassa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE1A3CEFF92FFB7FC5FF93FFB0B0887" author="Heard RW &amp; Manning RB" box="[949,1240,1667,1690]" pageId="55" pageNumber="500" pagination="883 - 888" refId="ref67516" refString="Heard RW, Manning RB. 1998. A new genus and species of ghost shrimp (Crustacea: Decapoda: Callianassidae) from the Atlantic Ocean. Proceedings of the Biological Society of Washington 111 (4): 883 - 888." type="journal article" year="1998">
<collectingCountry id="F3679EAFFF92FFB7FC5FF93FFC2E0884" box="[949,1021,1667,1689]" name="Heard Island and McDonald Islands" pageId="55" pageNumber="500">Heard</collectingCountry>
&amp; Manning (1998)
</bibRefCitation>
and then back to 
<taxonomicName id="4C70A5BCFF92FFB7FCD0F91EFC1108AA" authorityName="LEACH" authorityYear="1814" box="[826,962,1698,1719]" class="Malacostraca" family="Callianassidae" genus="Callianassa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="55" pageNumber="500" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B904022DFF92FFB7FCD0F91EFC1108AA" box="[826,962,1698,1719]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="500">Callianassa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE1A3CEFF92FFB7FC03F91FFB4908A5" author="Ngoc-Ho N" box="[1001,1178,1698,1720]" pageId="55" pageNumber="500" pagination="439 - 555" refId="ref73457" refString="Ngoc-Ho N. 2003. European and Meditterranean Thalassinidea (Crustacea, Decapoda). Zoosystema 25: 439 - 555." type="journal article" year="2003">Ngoc-Ho (2003)</bibRefCitation>
, who reviewed all Mediterranean and European species of the genus. 
<taxonomicName id="4C70A5BCFF92FFB7FA8BF97DFC2008E8" authorityName="GIARD &amp; BONNIER" authorityYear="1890" class="Malacostraca" family="Callianassidae" genus="Callianassa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="55" pageNumber="500" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="truncata">
<emphasis id="B904022DFF92FFB7FA8BF97DFC2008E8" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="500">Callianassa truncata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a widespread opportunistic species throughout much of the eastern Atlantic and the Mediterranean (
<bibRefCitation id="EFE1A3CEFF92FFB7FC29F8A1FA86092F" author="Abed-Navandi D &amp; Dworschak PC" box="[963,1365,1821,1843]" pageId="55" pageNumber="500" pagination="565 - 570" refId="ref60220" refString="Abed-Navandi D, Dworschak PC. 1997. First record of the thalassinid Callianassa truncata Giard and Bonnier, 1890, in the Adriatic Sea (Crustacea: Decapoda: Callianassidae). Annalen des Naturhistorischen Museum Wien 99 B: 565 - 570." type="journal article" year="1997">Abed-Navandi &amp; Dworschak, 1997</bibRefCitation>
; Ngoc- Ho, 2003; D. Felder, pers. comm.) and clearly is not endemic to vent or seep habitats.
</paragraph>
